item.title: about
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
CAFE

New York Style
café TT5 is a special place designed to emulate the stylish yet cozy atmosphere of a New York corner café. While incorporating urban industrial design, the space emphasizes the warmth of wood and natural light for a welcoming environment.

Tasty Coffee
We strive to bring a touch of luxury and relaxation to everyday life through a single cup of coffee. Our coffee beans are exclusively specialty coffee, carefully selected from producers worldwide. Each cup is brewed with care, using the optimal extraction method for the bean’s origin and roast level. Additionally, we offer a wide variety of handmade seasonal sweets and light meals to enrich your time at the café.

RENT SPACE

At café TT5, we offer a comfortable rental space that retains the stylish New York-style design of the café. The calm interior and spacious area filled with natural light provide flexibility for any occasion.

Designed for those who want to "create a special experience" or "bring their ideas to life," this space is perfect for a wide range of uses.

Features of the Space

Stylish Atmosphere
The space features an industrial design with brick walls, wooden tables, and iron-framed windows. Warm lighting and greenery add a blend of urban sophistication and tranquility.

Accommodates up to 15 People
From small groups to slightly larger workshops or events, the space can adapt to your needs. Seating and table layouts can be adjusted flexibly.

Well-Equipped

Projector and Screen
High-Speed Wi-Fi
Whiteboard
Audio Equipment (Speakers and Microphones)
We provide an environment that ensures easy preparation and a comfortable experience.

Exclusive Café Menu Service
Upon request, coffee and light meals can be served during your event. Catering options are also available for consultation.

Pricing Plans

Basic Rate

¥3,000/hour~
Discount plans are available for long-term or regular use.
Optional Services

Projector and Audio Equipment: ¥500/hour
Exclusive Café Menu (Light Meal & Drink Set): ¥1,000/person~
For more details, please contact us.
RECRUIT

Open Positions

Barista
Hall Staff
Kitchen Staff
Working Hours

Shift-based (Minimum 2 days per week, 4 hours per day; flexible scheduling)
Operating Hours: 10:00–18:00
Salary

¥1,100/hour~ (Negotiable based on experience and skills)
Qualifications

No experience required
Must enjoy coffee and customer service
How to Apply / Contact

Apply in person at the café
Reach out via our contact page

item.title: Easy and Fun for Beginners! Latte Art Workshop
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Event Overview

  • Date and Time: [Year] December Day 14:00–16:00
  • Fee: ¥3,000 (Tax included, includes 1 drink)
  • Capacity: 10 participants (First-come, first-served)
  • Eligibility: Beginners in latte art, coffee enthusiasts, adults

Event Details

Would you like to create your own latte art while learning professional barista techniques?
This workshop is designed for beginners and offers the following program:

Learn the Basics of Latte Art (15 minutes)

  • Explanation of how to make foamed milk and how to use basic tools.

Professional Demonstration (20 minutes)

  • Watch a barista demonstrate techniques for creating hearts and leaves.

Try It Yourself! Latte Art Experience (60 minutes)

  • Create your own latte art while making a café latte, with detailed guidance and advice.

Social & Sharing Time (15 minutes)

  • Capture your completed art in photos as a keepsake and enjoy connecting with other participants.

Host / Instructor Information

Barista Taro TT
Owner and barista of the popular local café TT5.
With over 10 years of experience, Taro specializes in clear and beginner-friendly teaching. Through professional insights, he brings the joy of latte art to all participants.

item.title: Delve Deep into the World of Coffee! Pro Barista's Exclusive Techniques
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Event Overview

  • Date and Time: 20**. **. ** 13:00–15:00
  • Fee: ¥4,000 (Tax included, includes 1 drink)
  • Capacity: 12 participants (First-come, first-served)
  • Eligibility: Coffee lovers, those looking to deepen their knowledge, adults

Event Details

Explore the profound appeal of coffee and discover ways to elevate your cup to new heights.
A professional barista will generously share techniques ranging from coffee basics to advanced methods.

Coffee Basics (20 minutes)

  • Learn about coffee bean varieties, roasting levels, and extraction fundamentals.
  • Experience differences in flavor and aroma while examining real coffee beans.

Extraction Demonstration (30 minutes)

  • Watch demonstrations of drip coffee, French press, and espresso brewing methods.
  • Learn tips and tricks specific to each brewing device.

Hands-On Session: Try It Yourself! (50 minutes)

  • Choose your preferred brewing method and brew your own coffee.
  • The barista will provide personalized advice to each participant.

Tasting and Discussion Time (20 minutes)

  • Sample your own coffee creation and share impressions with other participants.
  • Enjoy expanding your appreciation of coffee.

Host / Instructor Information

Barista Taro TT

  • A barista with over 15 years of experience in the coffee industry.
  • A multiple award-winner in competitions, known for his expertise and technical skills.
  • Dedicated to spreading the joy of coffee through numerous workshops.

Special Benefits

  • Each participant will receive 50g of the coffee beans used during the event as a gift!
  • Enjoy the experience of finding your favorite brewing method.

item.content:encoded:

An evening of acoustic live music in a cozy café.
Enjoy a special time where soothing music and aromatic coffee come together. Alongside the live performance, savor carefully selected drinks and sweets.

Fusion of Coffee and Music (19:00–)

  • A collaboration between musicians and baristas, introducing coffee that complements the music.

Relaxation Time (20:00–)

Special Benefits

  • Enjoy exclusive drinks from the live-event-only special menu.
  • All participants will receive a signed postcard from the artists!

item.title: Jazz & Coffee Night ~ A Special Evening at the Café ~

item.content:encoded:

item.title: Art Workshop at the Café ~ Painting Coffee Cups in Watercolors ~
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Event Overview

  • Date and Time: 20**. **. ** 14:00–16:00
  • Fee: ¥2,500 (Tax included, includes 1 drink)
  • Capacity: 8 participants (First-come, first-served)
  • Eligibility: Open to everyone, from beginners to art enthusiasts

Event Details

Enjoy the serene ambiance of a café while learning the basics of watercolor painting and creating a coffee cup artwork.
With guidance from an experienced instructor, even beginners can participate with ease!

Basic Watercolor Lesson (30 minutes)

  • Learn techniques such as mixing colors and essential watercolor skills.

Practice Time (90 minutes)

  • Use coffee cups as your motif and create your own watercolor painting.
  • The instructor will provide personalized advice to each participant.

Instructor Information

Instructor Name: Dan Noboru

  • A professional with over 10 years of experience teaching art workshops.
  • Known for his kind and thorough instruction, highly praised by participants.

Special Benefits

  • Take your completed artwork home as a keepsake!
  • Receive an exclusive original postcard, available only for participants.

item.title: Notice of Summer Holiday Closure
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Thank you for your continued support of café TT5.

We will be closed for summer holidays during the following period:

Holiday Period: Monday, August 12, 2024 – Thursday, August 15, 2024

We will resume normal operations starting Friday, August 16, 2024.

We hope you have a wonderful summer despite the hot weather. During the closure, reservations and inquiries will be addressed sequentially after we reopen.

We sincerely appreciate your understanding.

item.title: Notice of Golden Week Operating Days
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Thank you for your continued support of café TT5.

Here is our operating schedule during the Golden Week holiday period:

Operating Schedule:

  • April 29 (Mon, Holiday): Open as usual (10:00–18:00)
  • April 30 (Tue): Closed
  • May 1 (Wed, Holiday) – May 6 (Mon, Holiday): Open as usual (10:00–18:00)

We will be open as usual during Golden Week, offering delicious coffee and a relaxing atmosphere.

Due to expected crowds, we recommend making a reservation in advance before visiting.

We look forward to welcoming you!

item.title: blog
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:

Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)

...or something like this:

The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.

As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!
